<sect3 status="draft" id="vibrance"><title>Vibrance</title>
	<sect4><title>Overview</title>
		<informaltable frame="none"><tgroup cols="2" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
				<colspec colwidth="6*"/>
				<colspec colwidth="4*"/>
				<tbody>
					<row>						
						<entry>This modules affects the vibrance in the image. Vibrance is a widely used term
						and the endresult differs from program to program. Vibrance in darktable does 
						saturate the most saturated pixels and brings down the lightness of those pixels 
						to make the colors more vivid.
						</entry>
						<entry>
							<graphic fileref="darkroom/modules/images/vibrance.png" scalefit="1" width="80%" align="center" />
						</entry>
					</row>
				</tbody>
			</tgroup>
		</informaltable>
	</sect4>

	<sect4><title>Usage</title>
		<para>Vibrance does only have one parameter which controls the amount of vibrance to apply.
		</para>
		<sect5><title>vibrance</title>
			<para>The amount of vibrance to apply to the image.</para>
		</sect5>
	</sect4>

